dataIdInfo.idAbs: World Countries represents the boundaries for the countries of the world.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: World Countries provides a detailed basemap layer for the countries of the world. It has been designed to be used as a basemap and includes a Disputed Boundaries layer that can be used to edit boundaries to fit a user's needs. Included are fields for name, ISO code, FIPS code, capital, continent, and land type and rank.

report.measDesc: The dataset is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the dataset is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

The World Base Map was derived using Landsat 8, Landsat 7 (Global Land Survey (GLS) 2000 and GLS 2005), and SRTM (Shuttle Radar Topography Mission) as a global base. Landsat 7 provided the horizontal positional accuracy of +/- 50 meters 90% CE, and SRTM ensured that features appropriately fit the topography (i.e., rivers flowed through valleys).

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Copied the dataset from Data and Maps 2017 World Administrative Divisions. Dissolved features on the fields ISO_CC and LAND_RANK to create the country features. Cleaned up sliver polygons. Corrected fields to match Data and Maps 2017 World Countries by appending fields from World Countries, summarizing and renaming fields from World Administrative Divisions, and deleting fields not needed.
